The paper deals with fair allocation of resources, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing fair allocations, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses experiments on real-world data, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
